First thing I'm going to use this channel for is to give some examples of community mascots i think are successful or fun
starting off with a couple classic community mascots
Gnu mascot for the GNU project
Tux the Penguin for the Linux project
More complex mascot designs can be found in Japan where nearly every prefecture has their own
Wikipedia even has Wikipe-tan
Plenty of great designs to be found in the archives of the Olympic games, this is Vuƒçko from the 1984 Sarajevo Olympics
Hope this has helped someone looking for a place to start w an original Eco mascot!
mascot of random bank :eco_troll:
I good mascot for Eco is a planet, a planet like Earth. You can color the continents with Eco's logo colors.

Here are some thoughts for you. If you decide to go for a mascot that represents an animal, since humans will be your audience, you may have more success if you go for one animal that humans love the most. Some of the animals which bound with humans more easily hence having a chance of being loved by more humans are:
Dogs, Cats, Chickens, Pigs, Horses, Rabbits, Rats, Parrots, and Llamas.
I personally love Cats and Rabbits. Rabbits are super cute and amongst the top 3 more pleasant images humans like to look at in drawing/animations.
You can also go totally out of the norm and do a little green man from outer space. That could work!

Or you can represent an animal/insect that is of the most important for the Earth's *ecosystem*, that choice could be a metaphor for the importance of Eco in the survival of the ecommerce, which are Bees.
